==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muckworm
<hw>Muck"worm`</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧k"w⟦ucir⟧rm`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A larva or grub that lives in muck
or manure; -- applied to the larvae of the tumbledung and allied
beetles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who scrapes together money by mean labor and
devices; a miser.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Misers are <xex>muckworms</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mucky</ent>⟦br⟧
